It is understood the taxi carrying the children, aged between six and 10, veered off the road. JOHANNESBURG - Ten children have been injured in a minibus taxi accident in Randburg.It's understood the taxi carrying the children, aged between six and 10, veered off the road and drove down an embankment this afternoon.Officials say it appears the driver lost control of the vehicle.All the injured have been rushed to hospital and authorities have launched an investigation.ER24 s Russel Meiring says all the injured have been rushed to hospital. Several children were found walking around on the scene, while a few others were found seated under a nearby tree. We immediately assisted the patients and found that 10 of the 15 had sustained only minor injuries. Fortunately no serious or fatal injuries were reported on the scene. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)